WEBVTT

00:04.637 --> 00:06.773
[***]

00:06.806 --> 00:09.542
NARRATOR:
<i>Since I was the only black kid</i>
<i>at my school,</i>

00:09.576 --> 00:11.578
<i>I thought people stared at me</i>
<i>all the time</i>

00:11.611 --> 00:13.646
<i>because they were fascinated</i>
<i>with me.</i>

00:13.680 --> 00:14.848
Check it out.
His skin.

00:14.881 --> 00:16.349
Was your hair
always like this?

00:16.383 --> 00:17.717
Do you know
Gary Coleman?

00:17.751 --> 00:19.652
[STUDENTS CHATTERING]

00:19.686 --> 00:22.589
NARRATOR:
<i>But I found out they were</i>
<i>just scared of me.</i>

00:22.622 --> 00:24.691
[LOCK CLICKS]

00:24.724 --> 00:28.361
NARRATOR:
<i>She didn't come out of that</i>
<i>classroom for a whole week.</i>

00:28.395 --> 00:31.231
Can you tell me
what's going on?

00:31.264 --> 00:33.833
There's a rumor
about the fight.

00:33.867 --> 00:36.603
NARRATOR:
<i>I had a fight with Caruso,</i>
<i>the school bully.</i>

00:36.636 --> 00:38.338
<i>He beat me so bad,</i>
<i>I had to take</i>

00:38.371 --> 00:39.639
<i>the Underground Railroad</i>
<i>home.</i>

00:39.673 --> 00:41.641
STUDENTS [CHANTING]:
<i>Fight! Fight!</i>

00:41.675 --> 00:44.444
NARRATOR:
<i>But somehow that story</i>
<i>turned into this story:</i>

00:44.477 --> 00:47.580
Chris hit him in the jaw
so hard, my tooth fell out.

00:47.614 --> 00:49.249
Chris knocked
Caruso's eye out,

00:49.282 --> 00:51.317
put it back,
and then knocked it out again.

00:51.351 --> 00:53.253
Chris beat the snot
out of him.

00:53.286 --> 00:55.655
You can check his nose!
No snot!

00:55.689 --> 00:58.191
Chris chased him home,
knocked out his family,

00:58.224 --> 00:59.726
then took their house.

00:59.759 --> 01:02.295
NARRATOR:
<i>When a rumor like this</i>
<i>gets started,</i>

01:02.328 --> 01:04.297
<i>you never know where it's going</i>
<i>to end up.</i>

01:04.330 --> 01:05.732
Are you sure about this?

01:05.765 --> 01:08.468
Yes, sir. After Chris kicked
his teeth out, he said,

01:08.501 --> 01:11.438
"And I better not see you
trying to smile, cracker."

01:11.471 --> 01:12.605
Cracker...

01:12.639 --> 01:14.174
Yes, sir. Cracker.

01:14.207 --> 01:15.875
NARRATOR:
<i>Dr. Raymond</i>
<i>was the principal,</i>

01:15.909 --> 01:18.178
<i>and the last thing I needed</i>
<i>was for him</i>

01:18.211 --> 01:19.612
<i>to think</i>
<i>I was making trouble.</i>

01:19.646 --> 01:21.214
Thanks, kid.

01:21.247 --> 01:22.716
NARRATOR:
<i>That kid snitched so much,</i>

01:22.749 --> 01:24.751
<i>he made more money</i>
<i>than the teachers.</i>

01:24.784 --> 01:27.120
[***]

01:32.659 --> 01:35.729
<i>* Aw, make it funky now </i>

02:00.653 --> 02:02.589
[***]

02:03.757 --> 02:05.692
[HUMMING]

02:09.829 --> 02:11.231
Raise it up.

02:11.264 --> 02:12.932
Higher. Higher!

02:12.966 --> 02:15.835
Right there. That's good.
All right.

02:15.869 --> 02:19.572
NARRATOR:
<i>My brother Drew loved karate,</i>
<i>and he didn't take lessons.</i>

02:19.606 --> 02:22.375
<i>All he had to do was see</i>
<i>somebody do something,</i>

02:22.409 --> 02:23.777
<i>and then he could copy it.</i>

02:23.810 --> 02:26.312
<i>Today, you'd call that</i>
<i>a music producer.</i>

02:26.346 --> 02:28.548
[KARATE YELL]

02:29.883 --> 02:34.254
Chris! Breathe, breathe!

02:34.287 --> 02:36.423
Ah...
What are you doing?

02:36.456 --> 02:38.324
Practicing karate.

02:38.358 --> 02:40.293
What are you going
to do with karate?

02:40.326 --> 02:43.396
NARRATOR:
<i>My father didn't see the reason</i>
<i>of learning anything</i>

02:43.430 --> 02:45.565
<i>that didn't get you a job.</i>

02:51.504 --> 02:53.273
So how's school, Chris?

02:53.306 --> 02:56.276
You working on anthropology
or paleontology,

02:56.309 --> 02:58.278
something complicated, I bet.

02:58.311 --> 03:00.613
NARRATOR:
<i>My mother thought I was</i>
<i>learning all kinds of things</i>

03:00.647 --> 03:02.349
<i>'cause I went</i>
<i>to a white school.</i>

03:02.382 --> 03:03.850
Nope, it's just
regular arithmetic.

03:03.883 --> 03:06.586
Y'all hear that? White kids
are working on arithmetic.

03:06.619 --> 03:08.855
Around here,
they're still doing math.

03:08.888 --> 03:12.425
NARRATOR:
<i>My mother always thought bigger</i>
<i>words meant something better.</i>

03:12.459 --> 03:13.960
Okay, say the blessing, baby.

03:13.993 --> 03:15.495
Where's the meat?

03:16.996 --> 03:18.465
We don't have any.

03:18.498 --> 03:20.400
JULIUS:
Didn't you buy
some pork chops?

03:20.433 --> 03:22.302
No, that meat
was too expensive.

03:22.335 --> 03:26.373
JULIUS:
I know we got some canned Spam
or some Vienna sausage

03:26.406 --> 03:29.509
or bacon...
or beef jerky. Some...

03:29.542 --> 03:31.911
I mean, what kind of meal
is that without meat?

03:31.945 --> 03:33.480
It's a vegetarian meal.

03:35.615 --> 03:37.717
Do I look like
a vegetarian to you?

03:37.751 --> 03:39.452
I work 60 hours a week.

03:39.486 --> 03:41.588
I lift papers and boxes
all night.

03:41.621 --> 03:43.490
I don't want vegetables.
I need meat.

03:43.523 --> 03:45.492
Didn't you get paid today?

03:45.525 --> 03:47.494
I quit my job yesterday.

03:48.361 --> 03:50.030
Oh, I need you to be home

03:50.063 --> 03:51.398
early on Thursday

03:51.431 --> 03:53.066
so I can pick up
my check.

03:53.099 --> 03:54.601
How come you quit?

03:54.634 --> 03:56.903
They were disrespecting me,
Julius.

03:56.936 --> 03:59.773
NARRATOR:
<i>My father always</i>
<i>worked two jobs,</i>

03:59.806 --> 04:01.841
<i>which made my mother</i>
<i>so comfortable,</i>

04:01.875 --> 04:03.843
<i>she'd quit her job</i>
<i>over anything.</i>

04:03.877 --> 04:05.311
Check, please?

04:05.345 --> 04:06.613
NARRATOR:
<i>And I mean anything.</i>

04:06.646 --> 04:08.515
Now, do I look like I have
your check?

04:08.548 --> 04:10.450
All that hollering.
I don't need this.

04:10.483 --> 04:11.618
My husband has two jobs.

04:11.651 --> 04:13.386
I don't need to be here
right now.

04:13.420 --> 04:14.387
Hold my calls.

04:14.421 --> 04:15.889
Who are you hollering at?

04:15.922 --> 04:17.023
"Hold my calls."

04:17.057 --> 04:18.625
Hold your own damn call!

04:18.658 --> 04:20.727
I do not need this!
My man has two jobs!

04:20.760 --> 04:22.595
NARRATOR:
<i>My mother seemed to always</i>

04:22.629 --> 04:23.997
<i>find work when she needed it,</i>

04:24.030 --> 04:26.099
<i>so my father didn't complain</i>
<i>that much.</i>

04:26.132 --> 04:27.767
That's okay, baby.

04:27.801 --> 04:30.437
I guess all those other people
are just crazy.

04:32.038 --> 04:34.441
NARRATOR:
<i>That look means</i>
<i>"I know I'm wrong,</i>

04:34.474 --> 04:36.676
<i>but I'll be damned</i>
<i>if I'll admit it."</i>

04:40.080 --> 04:41.481
How about steak sauce?

04:41.514 --> 04:43.049
We got steak sauce?

04:43.083 --> 04:44.651
Hey, killer.

04:44.684 --> 04:47.687
[GRUNTING]

04:47.721 --> 04:48.688
Help me!

04:48.722 --> 04:51.458
I've heard what you've
been saying, Meadowlark.

04:51.491 --> 04:53.126
What? I haven't
been saying anything!

04:53.159 --> 04:55.762
You don't think I have enough
problems without people thinking

04:55.795 --> 04:58.431
I'm going around stomping
other people's teeth out?

04:58.465 --> 05:00.500
Do I need that?
Then who's been saying it then?

05:00.533 --> 05:04.471
NARRATOR:
<i>There's "Got your back" guys,</i>
<i>and "I'll be back" guys.</i>

05:04.504 --> 05:06.072
CHRIS:
Greg!

05:06.106 --> 05:09.642
NARRATOR:
<i>Greg was a "I'm running</i>
<i>like a bitch" guy.</i>

05:13.146 --> 05:15.849
You two,
in my office now.

05:15.882 --> 05:17.851
[BANGING]

05:17.884 --> 05:20.687
NARRATOR:
<i>Dr. Raymond hated his job</i>

05:20.720 --> 05:22.589
<i>because he didn't</i>
<i>get paid enough.</i>

05:22.622 --> 05:25.158
[DISCO SONG PLAYING]

05:25.191 --> 05:28.595
NARRATOR:
<i>So he blew off steam</i>
<i>by dancing the nights away</i>

05:28.628 --> 05:31.364
<i>with a few close friends.</i>

05:37.937 --> 05:39.572
[***]

05:39.606 --> 05:42.676
You think I like calling you
into my office?

05:46.146 --> 05:48.615
That's not
a rhetorical question.

05:48.648 --> 05:50.016
What's a rhetorical question?

05:50.050 --> 05:51.818
It's a question
that doesn't need an answer

05:51.851 --> 05:53.620
because you already know
the answer when you ask it.

05:53.653 --> 05:55.889
Who asked you?
Exactly.

05:59.459 --> 06:00.827
Now let me be clear.

06:00.860 --> 06:03.129
If I have any more trouble
from either of you,

06:03.163 --> 06:05.031
you're going to detention.

06:05.065 --> 06:07.667
NARRATOR:
<i>Detention was a step up</i>
<i>from my old school.</i>

06:07.701 --> 06:09.969
<i>In my old school,</i>
<i>if you did something wrong,</i>

06:10.003 --> 06:11.538
<i>you had to fight the principal.</i>

06:11.571 --> 06:13.006
You want to fight so bad?
Fight me!

06:13.039 --> 06:15.975
I ain't scared of you!
Well, bring it! Bring it!

06:16.009 --> 06:18.044
Oh, no, you didn't!
You, you, you--
Come on!

06:18.078 --> 06:19.879
NARRATOR:
<i>You should have seen</i>
<i>what happened</i>

06:19.913 --> 06:21.514
<i>when he tried to suspend her.</i>

06:21.548 --> 06:23.850
Why am I in trouble?
You heard.

06:23.883 --> 06:25.485
He beat me up.

06:25.518 --> 06:26.753
No, I didn't.

06:26.786 --> 06:28.755
And he called me
a white cracker.

06:28.788 --> 06:31.157
NARRATOR:
<i>Can you believe this cracker?</i>

06:31.191 --> 06:32.625
You got a point, son.

06:32.659 --> 06:35.428
Any more trouble,
that's detention.

06:36.663 --> 06:38.932
NARRATOR:
<i>Ain't this about a bitch?</i>

06:41.634 --> 06:43.603
What's this?
Meat.

06:43.636 --> 06:45.238
Fresh sausage links.

06:45.271 --> 06:47.040
I got a deal from the meat man.

06:47.073 --> 06:48.775
[***]

06:48.808 --> 06:50.643
NARRATOR:
<i>In Bed-Stuy,</i>
<i>"getting a deal"</i>

06:50.677 --> 06:53.046
<i>meant you bought something</i>
<i>that was stolen.</i>

06:53.079 --> 06:56.049
<i>Now, everybody knew the stuff</i>
<i>was stolen, which was cool,</i>

06:56.082 --> 06:59.552
<i>as long as it wasn't stolen</i>
<i>from you.</i>

06:59.586 --> 07:02.689
Hey! This is mine!

07:05.225 --> 07:07.027
MAN:
You better keep running, boy!

07:07.060 --> 07:09.195
Julius, look at all of this.

07:09.229 --> 07:12.966
We'll be eating sausage
every meal for a whole week.

07:12.999 --> 07:14.868
[SOFTLY]
If you hadn't quit your job,

07:14.901 --> 07:16.803
maybe we'd have variety.
Huh?

07:16.836 --> 07:20.206
Meat is good for society.

07:20.240 --> 07:22.108
[***]

07:22.142 --> 07:24.844
He said you
beat him up?

07:24.878 --> 07:27.681
Yeah, and I mean, like,
Raymond believed it.

07:27.714 --> 07:29.816
A hundred kids saw me
getting chased home.

07:29.849 --> 07:32.218
And now, everyone's
afraid of me.

07:32.252 --> 07:34.954
Caruso's already beaten
the heck out of me every day,

07:34.988 --> 07:36.956
and I can't even try
to defend myself

07:36.990 --> 07:39.059
without getting sent
to detention.

07:39.092 --> 07:40.860
You know, I can't take this.

07:40.894 --> 07:43.229
Well, why don't you
just punch him in the face?

07:43.263 --> 07:44.964
You did do it before.

07:44.998 --> 07:47.300
I didn't just walk up there
and pow, punch him in the face.

07:47.334 --> 07:48.735
I had a plan...

07:48.768 --> 07:50.637
which didn't include
getting beat down,

07:50.670 --> 07:52.305
chased home
and sent to detention.

07:52.339 --> 07:54.841
NARRATOR:
<i>It was like I was getting</i>
<i>my ass kicked</i>

07:54.874 --> 07:57.077
<i>for getting my ass kicked.</i>

07:57.110 --> 07:59.212
<i>Back at home,</i>
<i>my mother was cooking.</i>

07:59.245 --> 08:02.315
<i>I never knew how many meals</i>
<i>you could make with sausage.</i>

08:02.349 --> 08:04.017
<i>Chicken-fried sausage,</i>

08:04.050 --> 08:05.719
<i>sausage on a stick,</i>

08:05.752 --> 08:09.022
<i>kung-pao sausage.</i>
<i>But there was only one problem.</i>

08:09.055 --> 08:10.290
I hate sausage.

08:10.323 --> 08:12.726
Oh, come on, baby.
You haven't even tried it.

08:12.759 --> 08:14.861
That's 'cause
I hate sausage.

08:14.894 --> 08:16.329
NARRATOR:
<i>That look means</i>

08:16.363 --> 08:18.865
<i>"There's a smack over here,</i>
<i>if you want it."</i>

08:18.898 --> 08:21.568
Can she just eat
her vegetables?

08:21.601 --> 08:24.304
I thought vegetables
wasn't a meal.

08:25.839 --> 08:27.574
Now, I should send you
to Africa,

08:27.607 --> 08:29.275
since you don't want to eat.

08:29.309 --> 08:31.911
NARRATOR:
<i>My mother could deal</i>
<i>with a lot of things,</i>

08:31.945 --> 08:34.781
<i>but a child who wouldn't eat</i>
<i>was not one of them.</i>

08:34.814 --> 08:37.650
You're gonna sit there
until you eat that sausage.

08:39.252 --> 08:41.888
NARRATOR:
<i>That look means</i>
<i>"I'm still thinking about</i>

08:41.921 --> 08:44.124
<i>knocking you</i>
<i>out of that chair."</i>

08:49.062 --> 08:50.730
Go to bed, girl.

08:50.764 --> 08:53.233
NARRATOR:
<i>People go to war</i>
<i>over a lot of things:</i>

08:53.266 --> 08:58.805
<i>oil, land, lies, but this one</i>
<i>started over sausage.</i>

08:58.838 --> 09:01.274
[STUDENTS CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

09:01.307 --> 09:03.643
[GRUNTS]
Jeez, what was that?

09:03.677 --> 09:06.980
NARRATOR:
<i>At school, Caruso tortured me</i>
<i>every chance he got.</i>

09:07.013 --> 09:08.014
A battery!

09:08.048 --> 09:10.884
A D.
They're packing heavy.

09:10.917 --> 09:11.918
[SNICKERING]

09:11.951 --> 09:13.386
Come on, man.
Let's just go.

09:13.420 --> 09:15.355
No, no!

09:16.690 --> 09:18.992
I'm getting tired of him.

09:19.025 --> 09:20.960
[***]

09:23.363 --> 09:25.365
Look out!

09:30.437 --> 09:33.373
NARRATOR:
<i>If I'd have had a brick,</i>
<i>I'd have hit him.</i>

09:36.710 --> 09:39.346
<i>Maybe he didn't see</i>
<i>who threw it.</i>

09:39.379 --> 09:42.716
<i>Now, where were these guys</i>
<i>when Tupac got shot?</i>

09:45.118 --> 09:49.923
<i>* Everybody hates Chris </i>

09:54.794 --> 09:57.330
NARRATOR:
<i>After being beat down</i>
<i>and set up by Caruso,</i>

09:57.364 --> 09:59.933
<i>detention was about</i>
<i>the safest place I could be,</i>

09:59.966 --> 10:01.434
<i>as long I followed the rules.</i>

10:01.468 --> 10:03.837
The rules are clearly posted.
I suggest you read them.

10:03.870 --> 10:06.206
NARRATOR:
<i>The rules were simple:</i>
<i>you talk...</i>

10:06.239 --> 10:07.841
Ten minutes of detention.

10:07.874 --> 10:10.110
NARRATOR:<i>If you eat...</i>
Ten minutes of detention.

10:10.143 --> 10:12.445
NARRATOR:<i>If you sleep...</i>
Ten minutes of detention.

10:12.479 --> 10:14.814
NARRATOR:
<i>If you did anything</i>
<i>in detention</i>

10:14.848 --> 10:16.449
<i>other than sit down</i>
<i>and shut up...</i>

10:16.483 --> 10:18.218
Ten minutes of detention.

10:18.251 --> 10:20.353
NARRATOR:
<i>Since I was the new guy</i>
<i>in detention,</i>

10:20.387 --> 10:23.890
<i>everybody tried to get me</i>
<i>in more trouble.</i>

10:23.923 --> 10:26.359
What?
Ten minutes.

10:26.393 --> 10:27.727
But for what?

10:27.761 --> 10:29.963
Twenty minutes.

10:29.996 --> 10:32.132
[SNICKERING]

10:35.502 --> 10:38.204
NARRATOR:
<i>I didn't tell my mother</i>
<i>I was in detention,</i>

10:38.238 --> 10:40.206
<i>because then she'd come</i>
<i>up to school.</i>

10:40.240 --> 10:43.176
<i>And there's nothing worse</i>
<i>than a mad black woman</i>

10:43.209 --> 10:44.878
<i>at an all-white school.</i>

10:44.911 --> 10:47.480
I thought I told you to be here
so I pick up my check.

10:47.514 --> 10:49.015
I missed my bus.

10:49.049 --> 10:51.451
What were you doing
that you missed your bus?

10:51.484 --> 10:53.720
Uh, I...
uh, I just forgot?

10:53.753 --> 10:56.423
Oh. So you forgot
to come home?

10:56.456 --> 11:00.060
NARRATOR:
<i>I'll look pathetic</i>
<i>and she'll take pity.</i>

11:00.093 --> 11:00.927
<i>Uh-uh.</i>

11:00.960 --> 11:03.496
What's this?
It's a bucket and a mop...

11:03.530 --> 11:04.998
for mopping.

11:05.031 --> 11:07.000
Do the steps,
the bathroom and the hall.

11:07.033 --> 11:09.869
This'll help you to remember
to get your butt home on time.

11:09.903 --> 11:12.138
I'm going to pick up my check.

11:12.172 --> 11:14.007
[***]

11:14.040 --> 11:17.143
NARRATOR:
<i>After two days, Tanya hadn't</i>
<i>taken a bite of sausage.</i>

11:17.177 --> 11:19.879
<i>And after having it for</i>
<i>breakfast, lunch and dinner,</i>

11:19.913 --> 11:21.748
<i>she wasn't the only one</i>
<i>who hated it.</i>

11:21.781 --> 11:25.285
Mm...mm!
Now, this is good.

11:25.318 --> 11:27.120
Isn't it good, baby?

11:29.189 --> 11:31.925
Yeah. Yeah, it's good.

11:31.958 --> 11:33.059
Mmm!

11:33.093 --> 11:36.162
It's better than those
sausage-o's we had this morning,

11:36.196 --> 11:37.397
I'll tell you that.

11:37.430 --> 11:40.767
Well, anybody
want some cake?

11:40.800 --> 11:42.135
Does it have sausage in it?

11:42.168 --> 11:44.037
NARRATOR:
<i>We didn't usually have cake,</i>

11:44.070 --> 11:46.039
<i>but my mother was trying</i>
<i>to get at Tanya.</i>

11:46.072 --> 11:48.441
Can I have some cake?
You can have some sausage.

11:48.475 --> 11:50.477
NARRATOR:
<i>I told you.</i>

11:52.345 --> 11:54.981
Sausage.

11:55.015 --> 11:58.251
NARRATOR:
<i>Another day, another sausage.</i>

11:58.284 --> 12:00.353
Look, Tonya, if you
don't want sausage,

12:00.387 --> 12:03.523
then you're probably better off
eating lunch at school, then.

12:03.556 --> 12:05.558
I hate school lunch.

12:05.592 --> 12:07.927
You want some sausage?

12:07.961 --> 12:10.296
<i>Xie xie nin,</i>Mama.
What?

12:10.330 --> 12:12.465
It's "Thank you, Mom"
in Chinese.

12:12.499 --> 12:15.335
NARRATOR:
<i>When my brother got into</i>
<i>something, he got into it.</i>

12:15.368 --> 12:19.005
<i>You know, he's getting</i>
<i>Asian girls to this very day.</i>

12:19.039 --> 12:21.474
ROCHELLE:
Eh! Chris. I didn't get
my check yesterday

12:21.508 --> 12:23.309
because I was late
getting over there.

12:23.343 --> 12:25.845
I need you to have
your behind home on time.

12:25.879 --> 12:28.515
Do you understand me, boy?
Yes, ma'am.

12:28.548 --> 12:30.116
How many days
did you get?

12:30.150 --> 12:31.384
Three.

12:31.418 --> 12:32.585
[BELL RINGS]

12:32.619 --> 12:33.987
Ooh, I better
get in there.

12:34.020 --> 12:35.822
I can't be late
getting home today.

12:35.855 --> 12:37.057
You're late.
Ten minutes.

12:37.090 --> 12:38.825
But I was right
outside the door.

12:38.858 --> 12:40.260
Outside is not inside.
20 minutes.

12:40.293 --> 12:42.328
But--
Would you like
to try for 30 minutes?

12:42.362 --> 12:44.364
NARRATOR:
<i>I wonder how many</i>
<i>minutes I'd get</i>

12:44.397 --> 12:47.133
<i>for knocking her upside</i>
<i>the head with this book.</i>

12:50.103 --> 12:53.340
Mom-- School-- But--
No! Eh! Don't!

12:53.373 --> 12:55.442
NARRATOR:
<i>That look means,</i>
<i>"Get in this house</i>

12:55.475 --> 12:58.545
<i>before I smack the wax</i>
<i>out your ears."</i>

13:00.547 --> 13:02.582
[***]

13:06.152 --> 13:09.956
Baby, just try it.
It's good.

13:18.631 --> 13:22.235
NARRATOR:
<i>After a few days of sausage for</i>
<i>breakfast, lunch and dinner,</i>

13:22.268 --> 13:25.138
<i>would you believe my mother</i>
<i>started running out of ideas?</i>

13:25.171 --> 13:28.208
Mmm! Sausage and Pop-Tarts.

13:35.582 --> 13:38.585
You're eating the sausage.

13:46.159 --> 13:47.927
Can I talk to you
for a minute?

13:50.563 --> 13:53.199
Well, excuse me, children.

13:53.233 --> 13:55.402
Your father would like
to talk to me.

13:57.570 --> 13:58.972
Let's talk.

14:02.542 --> 14:04.077
Baby, if she doesn't eat,

14:04.110 --> 14:05.578
they could call
child welfare on us.

14:05.612 --> 14:08.181
Mm-mm, Julius, that
little girl is testing me.

14:08.214 --> 14:10.450
If I let her tell me
what she will and won't eat,

14:10.483 --> 14:12.485
the next thing you know,
she'll be telling me

14:12.519 --> 14:14.020
what she will
and won't wear.

14:14.054 --> 14:15.255
Next thing you know,
she'll be telling me

14:15.288 --> 14:17.090
when she will
and won't come home!

14:17.123 --> 14:19.192
The next thing you know,
she's going to end up pregnant,

14:19.225 --> 14:21.327
and I ain't taking care
of no babies.

14:21.361 --> 14:24.197
NARRATOR:
<i>My mother thought anything</i>
<i>that Tanya did wrong</i>

14:24.230 --> 14:25.598
<i>would eventually</i>
<i>get her pregnant.</i>

14:25.632 --> 14:27.934
<i>And she ain't taking care</i>
<i>of no babies.</i>

14:27.967 --> 14:29.202
But it's been two days.

14:29.235 --> 14:31.071
Oh, Julius,
it's been three days.

14:31.104 --> 14:33.973
Right. Three days.

14:34.507 --> 14:36.643
[***]

14:40.246 --> 14:42.949
Did you feed
her something?

14:48.688 --> 14:50.223
Here's a peanut
butter sandwich.

14:50.256 --> 14:52.359
When your mama comes down,
talk to the side,

14:52.392 --> 14:54.027
so she can't smell
your breath.

14:54.060 --> 14:55.962
And eat the crust.
I don't like crust!

14:55.995 --> 14:57.630
[SOFTLY]
I don't like crust.

14:57.664 --> 15:00.433
Just eat it, girl.

15:00.467 --> 15:03.203
NARRATOR:
<i>Would you believe my father</i>
<i>had to come back</i>

15:03.236 --> 15:05.071
<i>and finish the crust?</i>

15:05.105 --> 15:07.073
I'm sorry, baby.
Julius!

15:07.107 --> 15:08.742
I understand
what you're trying to do.

15:08.775 --> 15:11.277
[SIGHS]
We can put her on punishment.

15:11.311 --> 15:12.412
Whatever.

15:12.445 --> 15:14.214
I mean...
But we have to feed her.

15:14.247 --> 15:17.384
The next time, why don't you
let somebody know

15:17.417 --> 15:20.653
before you buy
a whole crate of sausage?

15:20.687 --> 15:22.422
Thank you!

15:24.357 --> 15:26.760
[SOFTLY]
Next time why don't you
let somebody know

15:26.793 --> 15:28.261
when you quit your job?

15:29.029 --> 15:30.030
I'm sorry?

15:30.063 --> 15:31.564
Hey, uh...

15:31.598 --> 15:33.133
I-I was going tell you...

15:33.166 --> 15:35.101
I'm-I'm going to get
chicken next time.

15:35.135 --> 15:36.736
My man got some hook-up
on the chicken.

15:36.770 --> 15:39.272
NARRATOR:
<i>Dr. Raymond pulled me</i>
<i>out of detention</i>

15:39.305 --> 15:41.007
<i>because he thought</i>
<i>talking to me</i>

15:41.041 --> 15:44.044
<i>would keep me out of trouble.</i>

15:44.077 --> 15:47.013
Son, I know things are rough
for you here.

15:47.047 --> 15:51.151
But just because
you don't have a father...

15:51.184 --> 15:53.687
But I do have a father.

15:53.720 --> 15:55.689
Well, when your mother
is on drugs...

15:55.722 --> 15:58.158
My mom's not on drugs.

15:58.191 --> 16:01.061
I understand, but being born
a crack baby is no excuse.

16:01.094 --> 16:03.563
I wasn't born a crack baby.
Look, son.

16:03.596 --> 16:05.498
I'm trying to help you.

16:05.532 --> 16:09.102
I know it's rough,
but I suggest you try to fit in.

16:09.135 --> 16:12.105
And the next time
you throw a battery,

16:12.138 --> 16:13.707
that's an automatic
suspension.

16:13.740 --> 16:15.275
Why do I have to get suspended?

16:15.308 --> 16:17.043
Caruso's the one
that started it.

16:17.077 --> 16:19.045
He's calling me names
and beating my butt

16:19.079 --> 16:20.280
every chance he gets.

16:20.313 --> 16:22.649
And I never called him
a cracker.

16:22.682 --> 16:24.284
[***]

16:24.317 --> 16:26.353
Are you sure about this?
Yeah.

16:26.820 --> 16:28.722
Good.

16:28.755 --> 16:31.391
NARRATOR:
<i>To this day, I don't know</i>
<i>if he believed me</i>

16:31.424 --> 16:33.093
<i>or he thought I was packing.</i>

16:33.126 --> 16:35.328
Stay out of trouble.

16:36.863 --> 16:38.198
So, what happened?

16:38.231 --> 16:40.166
Oh. Raymond let me go.

16:40.200 --> 16:41.735
But he thinks
I'm a crack baby.

16:41.768 --> 16:43.336
Listen, I just want
to get home.

16:43.370 --> 16:45.271
My mother is making
spaghetti tonight.

16:45.305 --> 16:48.208
NARRATOR:
<i>It was the only time</i>
<i>that week she made a meal</i>

16:48.241 --> 16:50.343
<i>that actually</i>
<i>went with sausage.</i>

16:50.377 --> 16:52.746
Hey, it's Tenspeed
and Brownshoe.

16:52.779 --> 16:56.082
What, no detention today?

16:56.116 --> 16:58.218
Look, why don't you
just leave me alone?

16:58.251 --> 16:59.853
I mean, what do
you want me to do?

16:59.886 --> 17:01.354
Go around
and tell everybody

17:01.388 --> 17:03.189
you beat the heck out of me?
Yeah.

17:03.223 --> 17:05.558
Fine. I'm just getting tired
of you messing with me.

17:05.592 --> 17:08.361
Oh, "I'm just getting tired
of you messing with me."

17:08.395 --> 17:11.097
NARRATOR:
<i>You just can't reason</i>
<i>with a bully.</i>

17:11.131 --> 17:13.500
I don't care.

17:13.533 --> 17:15.402
Greg...

17:15.435 --> 17:17.470
NARRATOR:
<i>I told you,</i>
<i>running like a bitch.</i>

17:17.504 --> 17:20.540
<i>I know it looks like</i>
<i>I'm taking the high road,</i>

17:20.573 --> 17:22.642
<i>but all I'm doing</i>
<i>is buying time.</i>

17:22.676 --> 17:24.844
<i>Remember, bullies</i>
<i>are kind of like dogs.</i>

17:24.878 --> 17:29.115
<i>They usually don't chase you</i>
<i>unless you run.</i>

17:29.149 --> 17:31.251
[***]

17:32.919 --> 17:34.254
What are you doing?

17:34.287 --> 17:36.256
I'm getting revenge.

17:36.289 --> 17:38.158
<i>* You can't hide </i>

17:38.191 --> 17:39.626
BOY:
Think he went outside?

17:45.165 --> 17:47.300
[NECK CRACKING]

17:49.169 --> 17:51.271
[YELLING]

17:54.708 --> 17:58.178
NARRATOR:
<i>Just how long is he going</i>
<i>to wait to stop this?</i>

18:01.815 --> 18:03.249
All of you.

18:03.283 --> 18:04.551
In my office.

18:04.584 --> 18:06.686
Now.

18:06.720 --> 18:09.322
[***]

18:09.356 --> 18:11.191
Pick that stuff up.

18:12.592 --> 18:14.694
NARRATOR:
<i>Despite numerous</i>
<i>internal injuries,</i>

18:14.728 --> 18:19.199
<i>seeing Caruso go to detention</i>
<i>still felt good.</i>

18:23.536 --> 18:25.805
<i>That night,</i>
<i>I got home on time,</i>

18:25.839 --> 18:27.440
<i>my mother got her check,</i>

18:27.474 --> 18:29.843
<i>but Tanya still wouldn't</i>
<i>eat her sausage.</i>

18:29.876 --> 18:34.314
[SIGHS]
Baby, just try it, okay?

18:34.347 --> 18:35.882
But I don't like it.

18:35.915 --> 18:38.818
ROCHELLE:
But if you don't try it,
you'll never know.

18:38.852 --> 18:42.589
I didn't used to like
your father, and now I do.

18:42.622 --> 18:44.491
And I definitely
didn't like you, Tanya.

18:44.524 --> 18:45.725
[CHUCKLES]

18:45.759 --> 18:46.893
I never liked Drew.

18:46.926 --> 18:48.261
And I hated your mother.

18:48.294 --> 18:50.430
[ALL LAUGHING]

18:50.463 --> 18:51.898
Come on, baby,
you can do it.

18:51.931 --> 18:54.601
Just try it.
A little bit.

18:54.634 --> 18:56.336
Okay.

18:56.369 --> 18:58.571
[***]

19:07.714 --> 19:08.882
It's good.

19:08.915 --> 19:11.618
[ALL CHEER]

19:11.651 --> 19:13.787
NARRATOR:
<i>Now I'd love to sit here</i>
<i>and tell you</i>

19:13.820 --> 19:15.689
<i>that we had the sort of</i>
<i>loving family</i>

19:15.722 --> 19:17.457
<i>that worked out all</i>
<i>its problems</i>

19:17.490 --> 19:19.559
<i>with love, compassion</i>
<i>and patience,</i>

19:19.592 --> 19:22.328
<i>that we ended every day</i>
<i>with hugs and laughter,</i>

19:22.362 --> 19:25.398
<i>but here's what really</i>
<i>happened that night...</i>

19:28.535 --> 19:32.806
[SIGHS]
Baby, just try it, okay?

19:32.839 --> 19:34.407
But I don't like it.

19:34.441 --> 19:35.975
You're going to eat
this sausage!

19:36.009 --> 19:37.777
Do you hear me?
Girl, do you think

19:37.811 --> 19:39.379
I'm playing with you?

19:39.412 --> 19:41.247
JULIUS:
Oh, no! No! Rochelle!

19:41.281 --> 19:42.916
No! Rochelle!
[TONYA SCREAMING]

19:42.949 --> 19:45.251
Rochelle, no,
no, no, no!

19:45.285 --> 19:47.554
NARRATOR:
<i>It took us about an hour</i>
<i>to get my mother off</i>

19:47.587 --> 19:49.556
<i>of Tanya's behind,</i>
<i>but eventually,</i>

19:49.589 --> 19:51.458
<i>Tanya did eat her sausage.</i>

19:51.491 --> 19:53.793
<i>And as for my mother,</i>
<i>well, to this very day,</i>

19:53.827 --> 19:57.364
<i>she still ain't raising</i>
<i>no babies.</i>

19:57.397 --> 19:59.966
<i>* A dream come true </i>

20:01.768 --> 20:03.703
[***]

20:05.305 --> 20:08.508
<i>* Aw, make it funky now </i>
